I want to help kids. That is why I want to be a social worker. I want to work with the Division of Family and Children Services. I want to help kids who have been hurt or not taken care of. I also want to help families who are having problems.

I think it is important to be kind to people. I think it is important to do the right thing. I want to help people get along better. I also want to learn more about how to help people.

I have always wanted to help people. But I was not sure what to do. In high school and college, I saw people who had problems. Some people tried to hide their problems. Others used bad ways to deal with their problems. 

After I graduated from college in 2009, I met a boy. He was 16 years old. He was staying with a friend because he was being hurt by his parents. I wanted to help. I talked to the police. The police asked me to talk to the boy’s parents.

When I talked to the parents, they seemed afraid. They said the boy was lying. I realized that I wanted to be a social worker so I could help kids like this boy.

It is also important to be fair to everyone. Everyone is important. We should treat everyone the same. 

I have always believed in being fair and helping people. In high school and college, I showed my support for being fair. I did this by dressing in a way that showed who I was. I joined a group that supported gay and straight people. I spoke out against racism and unfair treatment. I will continue to fight for what is right.

This paper looks at two ways to understand sleep problems: the body's biology and the person's social world. The biology model looks at genes and how the body works. The sociocultural model looks at how a person's life, like where they live and their job, can cause sleep problems. The paper will look at research that uses both models to understand sleep problems. The paper will also say what is good and bad about each study.

Sleep problems can be caused by many things. Sometimes they are the main problem. Other times they are a part of a bigger problem, like stress or depression. Sleep problems can also be caused by medical problems or taking medicine.  

There are two main types of sleep problems: trouble sleeping (dyssomnias) and strange things happening while sleeping (parasomnias). Trouble sleeping includes insomnia (trouble falling asleep), hypersomnia (sleeping too much), narcolepsy (falling asleep suddenly), breathing problems when sleeping, and problems with your body's natural sleep clock. Strange things happening while sleeping include nightmares, sleep terrors, sleepwalking, and other unusual things that happen during sleep.

Sleep problems can also be caused by mental health problems, like depression or anxiety. This paper will mostly focus on insomnia and how the biology and sociocultural models help us understand it.


The biology model looks at how genes, the body's chemistry, and how our brains work can cause sleep problems. One study looked at mice and found that a part of the brain that controls sleep has special receptors that can be turned on or off. When these receptors are turned on, the mice feel sleepy. When they are turned off, the mice are more awake. This study shows that there are parts of the body that control sleep. If these parts don't work right, it can cause sleep problems. This could be caused by genes or by problems with the body's chemistry. The study also shows that things in the environment can affect these receptors. This means that people's lives and experiences can also affect their sleep. [

This paper talks about Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD). First, we look at what CAPD is. Next, we talk about how doctors find out if someone has CAPD. Finally, we talk about how a teacher can help a student with CAPD in a regular classroom. 

Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD), or Auditory Processing Disorder (APD), means the brain has trouble using sound. People with CAPD can hear sounds, but their brain has trouble making sense of them. The part of the brain that helps us understand words and sounds is not working well. 

Doctors first talked about CAPD in the 1950s. They called it "auditory imperception". Doctors started making tests for it in the 1950s and 1960s. A big meeting about CAPD happened in 1977.

CAPD can show up in many ways. A person with CAPD may not be able to tell where a sound is coming from. They may have trouble telling different sounds apart. They may have trouble understanding patterns in sounds. They may not understand changes in someone's voice. They may miss sounds if another sound comes right after it. They may have trouble putting together sounds to understand what someone is saying. They may have trouble remembering the order of sounds.

To find out if someone has CAPD, a doctor will watch how they listen and give them tests. Audiologists, speech therapists, and psychologists can give these tests. There is no one test that always works. There is also no known cause for CAPD.

The play Twelfth Night says that disguise is good for tricking people, but it can be bad in the end. People must choose their true self or stay in disguise. If they tell the truth, people may be angry.

Disguises about gender are hard. Why does someone want to be the opposite gender? In Viola’s story, she is a woman who disguises herself as a man. She does this to stay safe in a new land.

Viola’s plan works, but she loses friends. She is so good at being a man that Olivia thinks she is a man named Sebastian and falls in love with her. Viola also has feelings for Orsino, but she cannot show them.

Twelfth Night shows that hiding can help people see their true feelings. Olivia and Orsino may like Viola more because she is disguised. Shakespeare may be showing how people can hide their feelings. For example, is Olivia attracted to Viola because Viola looks like a man, or does Olivia like women? It is hard to say. Olivia may be making fun of people who judge others by their looks. She quickly falls in love with Sebastian after liking Viola.

Twelfth Night shows that hiding can be tricky.

German rule in Africa was hard on the people who lived there.  

In South West Africa (now Namibia), the German people did bad things to the Ovaherero and Nama people. This is true, but it is not the whole story of German rule.

German rule in Africa was different in each place. Some places had good schools for Africans. When the British took over German East Africa (now Tanzania) in 1919, they saw many Africans who could read and write. 

But in South West Africa, things were different. The German government did not help African people go to school. The German government helped European people go to school.

This had a big effect on South West Africa even after Germany stopped ruling there. While other German colonies had many educated Africans, most Africans in South West Africa could not read or write. 

Many things caused this. This paper will look at these things and talk about what the German settlers and leaders thought about African people.


There are many books about education in German colonies. Most of these books are in German and were written a long time ago. They talk about the different schools in the colonies. Later books in English compared schools in different colonies. These books showed that schools were very different.

One book looks at education in South West Africa and East Africa. It says that South West Africa had many European settlers, and this is why schools were different there.

South West Africa was a good place to live. More European people lived there than in any other German colony.

Popular music has many kinds of music. There are many, many kinds. It is hard to list them all.  

Some kinds are rap, rock, country, jazz, and folk. Each of these kinds has many smaller kinds. Heavy metal is one kind that is very big now. It started about 40 years ago. 

Heavy metal has many feelings. They are often dark feelings. It is also very different. Many people make their own kinds of heavy metal. New kinds are still being made.

Now there are so many kinds of heavy metal that it is hard to say what heavy metal really is. It has borrowed from other kinds of music. But it started somewhere.

To understand heavy metal, we need to know what it is and why it is a movement, not just a kind of music.

Heavy metal is a movement about darkness. It has loud music, strong bass, and loud drums. It is also very musical. The people who play in metal bands are good musicians. 

Heavy metal also uses drugs. In the 1970s, people used many drugs. This made the music strange and new. 

Heavy metal is dark and strong. This was new in music because most music was not dark.

Young people who like heavy metal also like the dark music from a long time ago. Songs from that time are called Romantic music. Some examples are:

(Byrne) 

These words are from a song by the Beatles called "Helter Skelter." It has a dark feeling and is about drugs.  Some people say this is one of the first heavy metal songs. The Beatles wanted to be as heavy as the Rolling Stones.

Henri Rousseau was an artist. He made art that was like dreams. Before artists like the Surrealists, Rousseau made art about dreams. His painting, The Dream, shows a woman in a dream.  It also shows what Rousseau wanted. He wanted people to like his art.

Rousseau wanted to be a famous artist.  He wanted to be liked by other artists. But he also wanted to make art his own way. He had a hard time because the art world had rules. To be liked, he had to paint like other artists.  But he wanted to be different. The painting The Dream shows this hard time.

Rousseau was born in France in 1844. He did not go to art school. He worked for the government.  He lost his wife and children. He started painting when he was older. He wanted to make art that was different.

Rousseau wanted to be liked by art people. He was not as famous as other artists. He started making art when Matisse was already famous. 

Matisse made modern art. Rousseau wanted to make art that people would like. He wanted to be in a group called the Artiste Français.

Many thinkers say that good ideas and good art are close.  I think this is true. John Keats said, “Beauty is truth, truth beauty- That is all / Ye know on earth, and all ye need to know.”  We learn much from school and life. But we seem to know good and bad art without being taught. 

Good and bad art and good and bad actions are both ways to explain things. We try to say why art is good or why an action is right.  We do not just make rules for art and being good. 

If we talk about a good painting, we might talk about colors and shapes. But this does not say why it is good. When someone asks about a good book, they often say, “There is something about it.” We cannot fully explain art. 

Flannery O'Connor said, “A story is a way to say something that can't be said any other way.” We can describe a story, but there is still something special. 

I think ethics is like this too. It is hard to say what is right and wrong.

I think good art and good morals are special because we feel them deeply. It is hard to explain this feeling. Literature is good because it has morals. 

Literature is like life. It has values.

Germany is a strong country today. It has a special culture.  You can feel this culture in many places, from Munich in the mountains to Kiel by the Baltic Sea.  You can see it in Cologne on the Rhine River and in Dresden on the Elbe River. Germany's culture comes from many different people and tribes.

The land of the Germans is called Germania.  Scholars do not agree on where the name comes from.  Tacitus, a Roman writer, said the name came from a German tribe called the Tungrians. They were called Germans before they crossed the Rhine River and fought the Gauls. Julius Caesar first used the word "Germanus" in his writings about the Gallic Wars. He used it to talk about the people he had not conquered, unlike the Gauls whom he had defeated. Some people think the word came from a Gaulish word for "neighbor." 

 In his book about the Gallic Wars, Caesar writes: "The Germans, who live beyond the Rhine, are often at war with them (the Gauls). They fight the Germans almost every day." Others think the name comes from a spear they used in war, called a ger, or from an old Irish word meaning "to shout."

The Roman historian Tacitus wrote about the Germans in 98 AD. He said they were a separate people and not mixed with others. He said, “Who would leave Asia or Africa for Italy for Germany, with its wild country, its bad weather, its unfriendly people, unless it were their home?” 

The Romans mostly stayed away from Germania. They took goods from the land and sometimes fought wars there, but they mostly went home to their big empire. In the first century AD, Germanic tribes lived near the Roman Empire. They traded goods and some even joined the Roman army.

I look down. I see the thing in front of me.  My mind tries to understand. It looks but does not feel. My thoughts go in and out fast. My mind works well. It is like water. Smooth and clean.

Once, an artist told me to get a book. The book is called "The New Drawing on the Right Side of the Brain." I wanted to draw when I was small. This book teaches much. It teaches about pencils and how the brain sees lines.

One way is to put a square around a picture.  A big picture, like a bowl of fruit on a table, becomes a small picture, just the bowl.

Now, I look at the bowl. I cannot use the square. It is too much. I am amazed.

Picasso was blue. Monet loved green. Artists use many colors. This is my start. My picture. Brown.

My hand holds the thing I will use to make art. My muscles move. My mind makes a shape. Maybe this is the best moment of my life.

Water swirls. It is calm and clear. Things break off and go away.

My hand gets tight. It moves fast. I hit the thing again. It will not move.

I hold a mop. My tie is tight. I frown. The thing is brown and bad. Someone left it for me.

I flush the water more. I think. Then I take the paper. I wrap it around my hand.

I stand up. I bend. My hand goes into the water.  Like a mother in an oven.

Teenagers are dying in car accidents. Many things cause this problem. The National Institutes of Health say the teen brain is not ready for driving dangers.  Teenagers also lack experience. This causes more accidents, rollovers, speeding, and driving off the road.

Teens are more dangerous when they drive with friends. This is common. A study by the Southern California Injury Prevention Research Center showed a link between passenger age and accidents.

States try to make teen driving safer with permits. These permits limit driving hours and passenger numbers. But these are temporary fixes.

The problem is teenagers are not good drivers. Psychologist Marvin Zuckerman says 18 is too young to drive. He says young people want to take risks. It makes sense to wait until they are older to get a license.

If we do not change the rules, more teens will die in car crashes. Many teenagers will get licenses soon.

We need new laws. Schools can teach driving, but no one under 18 can drive. Permits can be given before a full license. Teens must practice.

We should have the same rules in every state. This will help protect teens everywhere.

I looked at old films from the Library of Congress. I saw fifteen trick films from 1895 to 1901. These films use movie cuts to make things seem magic. I looked at how the films made magic tricks work. I also looked at how some films from later in this time used new ways to make tricks. 

Most trick films from this time are made inside a set. The camera does not move. The shots are long and show a lot of the scene. The filmmakers used one shot for each trick.  

Many trick films have actors in front of a stage. The camera does not move to follow them. This is like old plays and magic shows.  The actors can only move side to side. They do not walk towards or away from the camera. For example, in the film “Uncle Josh in a Spooky Hotel” (1900), the actors walk back and forth. The camera does not follow them.

Because the camera does not move, the shots are long or medium. Close-ups are never used. This is like old plays, where the audience could see the whole thing at once.

Most trick films are one shot long. This means they are short, maybe one minute or less. They often show short tricks like magic or making things disappear.  But, remember, one shot in the film may be many shots put together to make a trick work.

Look at “The Execution of Mary, Queen of Scots” (1895). It seems like one long shot, but if you look closely, you can see where the magic trick happens.

John Taylor from Caroline was a strong supporter of early Republican ideas.  He worked on farms, and this job, along with his short time in politics, made him known for his strong beliefs about personal freedom and government. He believed strongly in farming.  Almost all his ideas about government came from this belief. He wanted to protect and help farming, and this shaped his views on important things like how much power the government should have and how the courts should work.

John Taylor thought the United States had a good chance to make the best kind of government because there were no old ways to stop them. This meant they could create a system of self-government. He strongly believed in people's natural rights and that they are all connected. If one right is taken away, then they all become weaker. These rights should be safe from the government. He said that what some people call the "state of nature" meant strong people and clever people did well, but in a society, this should not be true.

To make this ideal society, Taylor thought the government should be made to understand that people are both good and bad. He was very firm in his beliefs about good and evil. He said, "As government is exercised by man, all its virtues and vices must be human." He said good things for government are protecting private property, helping farming, and not supporting big businesses. He thought a good government would work fairly no matter who was in charge, even though leaders are always greedy and think of themselves first. He thought people are always motivated by what's good for them, but this is only bad when it leads to groups of people who do well at the expense of others. A good government is needed to keep people from being too bad, and even then, it has to be watched carefully to make sure it doesn't become bad.

Taylor, like many other strong Republicans of his time, wanted the Constitution to be followed very closely. He wanted a small Federal government, with only the power the Constitution gave it. He knew a big government would be expensive and could become too powerful. But he also thought a simple, word-for-word interpretation was dangerous. Without understanding what the writers of the Constitution meant, it could easily be misused. He thought the Declaration of Independence was the real guide for the United States because it said more clearly that the country was made up of separate states, not one nation.

The number of commuter logs went down a lot in the third month. This was sad. We do not know why this happened. It could be that winter came to the college. Fewer people ride bikes or walk in the winter. December is also the end of fall classes. Students are busy with schoolwork and grades. They may have forgotten to fill out the log. December is also a busy time for holidays. Students and teachers have a long break. Many people do not come to college. Classes start again in late January. This may explain why there were few logs in January. But this does not explain why there were few logs in February.

Maybe people were less excited about the project after a while. To fix this, we had a special week in March called Carpool Challenge Week. We wanted to make people more excited about the project. This worked, and more people filled out logs. One problem was keeping people interested. People have to deal with holidays and school breaks.

Another problem was that people like to drive cars. This is part of our culture. We need to give people reasons to use other ways to get around. We gave away prizes like gift cards. It would be interesting to see if bigger prizes would work. Maybe a bicycle, a car that uses less gas, or an electric car would help. We did not change the prizes during the project. 

Maybe if we had given away better prizes, more people would have participated. We started with good prizes, but maybe if we had said we would give away bikes in December and a car in January, more people would have joined.

An ETF is a type of security. It tracks an index, a good, or a group of things like an index fund. But it is more flexible. It trades like a stock. An ETF gives you the spread of an index fund and the good things about owning a single stock. You can sell short, buy on margin, and buy just one share. ETFs cost less to own than regular funds. But you have to pay a fee to buy or sell an ETF.  There are many different ETFs to choose from.

It is good to check if the good things an ETF says it has, like spread, are really true. We will look at an ETF called IHF. We will compare it to the top ten things in the ETF. 

We will look at the top ten things in the ETF because they make up most of it.  

To see how good the top ten things are at showing how the ETF works, we can use the % of money they have. We can use this to see how much each thing helps the ETF's risk and return. 

The chart shows the return and risk of a group made up of just the top ten things. 

The top ten things have a return that is 6.11% higher than the ETF.  This is a big difference. The top ten things also have less risk than the ETF. 

It looks like owning just the top ten things might be a better way to invest. But we need to be sure. Maybe the difference is not real.  

To know for sure, we need to look at how much each of the top ten things changes in price.

"Dream-Land" is one of Edgar Allan Poe's best poems. In the poem, Poe uses the word "Thulé" in two places. Poe took the word from the writer Virgil. Virgil used it for an island north of Britain. The Greeks thought this island was the edge of the world. Poe liked German writers. 

One expert, Karl J. Arndt, says Poe copied a poem by the writer Goethe. The poem is called "The King of Thulé". The poem is about a king who loses his wife. He drinks too much and cries for her. He decides to die and gives his things to his children. He throws a special cup into the ocean and kills himself. The king in "Dream-Land" is like the king in Goethe's poem.

Goethe was very famous. He wrote a play called "Faust". The first part was published in 1808 and the second part in 1832. There is a short poem in the second part of "Faust" called "The King of Thulé". 

Poe used the word "Thulé" in two of his poems. He used it in "Dream-Land" at the beginning and end of the poem. The poems "Dream-Land" and "The King of Thulé" are connected. The speaker in "Dream-Land" talks about Thulé. He says it is dark and lonely. He is with dead friends and sees a world without color.

Poe liked Tennyson. He would have known Goethe because of Tennyson. Poe would have also known Goethe from other copies of his work.

In California, a person hurt in a store can ask for extra money (called punitive damages) if the store manager did something very wrong. To get this extra money, the hurt person (the plaintiff) must show the manager knew the danger and did not care.

A judge will not quickly throw out Jennifer Palmer's case. She says the store manager, Martin, had a chance to clean up the applesauce spill but did not. He knew about the spill twice but said he was eating dinner.  Palmer can say that Martin should have known a spill is dangerous. Other people had slipped and fallen at the store before.

Palmer says Martin's actions were very bad (despicable). She can show that many people fell in the store before her accident, and Martin still did not make it safer.

On October 13, 2009, at 5:00 pm, an employee told Martin about the spill. Martin said he was eating and did not have time. Later, another employee told Martin again, but he said the same thing.

At 5:30 pm, Palmer fell and hurt her back. Before her accident, five other people fell in the store that year. Palmer is suing the store for money for her injury and for extra money because Martin was mean.

California law says a person can get extra money if the store acted badly.  The law says the store must have acted with anger, tricks, or meanness. The law also says the store must have known its actions were dangerous and did not care.  A judge has said that a store manager is mean if he knew people could be hurt and did not try to stop it.

Four years ago, I took a class about Islam at CBC. We talked a lot about if Islam was a bad religion. This is still a very important question. After 9/11, the way people showed Islam on TV changed a lot.  First, it was very negative. Now, it is very positive.  I do not think we could have had a president named Barack Obama, who has Muslim family, in 2001.

I am interested in the story of the Prophet Muhammad.  What I know about his life seems different from what is written in his biography. I thought Muhammad forced people to become Muslim. He would take over groups of people and make them follow Islam. But the biography makes him seem like a good man who was misunderstood. People came to him and learned about Islam on their own.

There are some things that are similar between Jesus and Muhammad. For example, Muhammad changed small amounts of food into a lot of food for many people. This makes it seem like the writers want people to see Muhammad as a good prophet. They want people to think he did not need to prove anything, but just lived a true life. This is bad because it makes Jesus's miracles seem less important. It is like they are copying Jesus.

There are many stories in the biography that say people became Muslim on their own. But many of these stories are told by people who heard them from someone else. This makes the stories less believable. 

The most important thing to me is that the biography tries to make Muhammad seem like a good and humble man. But history shows that Muhammad was not always gentle and humble. I wonder if Muslims today know the real story about Muhammad's life.

Jesus’ ideas changed the world, but his teachings changed over time.  Today, many people want to go back to the original ideas of Jesus. They want to know what Jesus really said. It will take time, but people will learn more about Jesus’ real teachings.

Many people will want to follow Jesus’ ideas exactly. They will want to read his words in a new way. This will make Christianity more simple. There will be less fighting between different groups of Christians.  

History shows us that things can change. For example, the Roman Empire hurt Christians, but then became a Christian empire. In the United States, we went from slavery for Black people to Black people leading our country.

The future of Christianity will be a return to its roots. People will want to know what Jesus truly taught.  They will read his words in a new way.  This will make Christianity more like it was when Jesus first started teaching.

The book "The Jungle" shows that people can be greedy. They want good things for themselves, but they do not care about others. The owners of big factories are a good example. They want to make their factories big and successful. They do not care if people or animals are hurt. The book says that the factories are big and black. Smoke goes up from them into the sky. The owners do not care about the smoke or the dirty water from the pens where animals are kept. The owners also do not care about the workers. They want to make as much money as possible. They make workers do hard jobs for long hours. They can fire people without warning. There were not many laws to protect workers at that time. So, the owners could treat workers very badly. The workers had no help. There were unions, but they did not help the workers much. The workers were treated like slaves.

Many writers use ways to make readers feel a certain way about things. Some ways are better than others. F. Scott Fitzgerald uses many ways in his book *The Great Gatsby*. He sometimes uses words together that do not usually go together to make a feeling. He also uses symbols to make feelings. Fitzgerald uses colors like gold, green, white, gray, and red/pink. In his book, he gives meaning to these colors and then uses them to make readers think of a feeling when they see something.

Fitzgerald uses the colors white/gray to mean sameness. White is a bit nicer and shows class, while gray is older and faded. He shows this in the beginning of the book. Daisy and Jordan are always wearing white. Nick wears white clothes to Gatsby's party. Tom wears a white shirt when he meets Myrtle. Catherine is white. The only time people do not wear white is when Nick goes to Gatsby's party, which has lots of bright colors. Fitzgerald shows these colors in normal things too. Nick goes down white streets to work. The names of people at Gatsby's party are gray on his list. Catherine's apartment is like a white cake. He also uses white and gray for simple people or things.  Jordan and Daisy had white childhoods. There are gray cars and gray land in the valley of ashes. The Italian boy is gray. The dog-seller is an old gray man.

After Fitzgerald gives these colors meaning, he uses them to show that something is not important or is the same. He does this with Daisy. After a long time without using these colors, Fitzgerald describes Daisy in a white car.  Readers start to see Daisy as less of a person and more like something Gatsby wants. Fitzgerald uses white with Daisy again to make her look like a part of a whole. There is a gray haze on her fur collar, and she is in a white dress before Tom and Gatsby meet.

San Diego is good for farming. The weather is warm and sunny. Farmers grow many things there, like tomatoes, oranges, lettuce, squash, broccoli, herbs, peaches, lemons, berries, honey, and peppers. Many people in San Diego want to buy food from farms that do not use chemicals.  There are many groups that sell this food, and they have long waiting lists.  Many people also like to buy organic eggs and milk. Many organic farms show people around their farms. They also let people walk, look for birds, and do other activities.

This is good for the farmer because they can get help from the government. They can also help animals and plants. They can make money by giving tours and teaching people about farming.

Organic farming is good for animals and plants because it does not use chemicals.  
But, organic farming can be expensive. It needs more work to keep pests away and to make the soil good. Sometimes, organic farms lose more food than farms that use chemicals. Small organic farms are not as big as other farms, so they cannot grow as much food.  

There are other things that farmers can do that are good for animals and plants. These things cost more money. Some examples are planting special plants to help animals, moving animals around to different areas, getting rid of bad plants, and making sure that plants grow in the right way.

So, there are many reasons why a farmer might want help to make money and to help animals and plants.

This story is about a piece of land near a town called Potrero in San Diego County. It is 160 acres of chaparral, grass, and oak trees. It is near a big forest. This land is important for many plants and animals. Some of them are in danger of disappearing.


This land was used by Native Americans for a long time. Then, people who raise cattle and cut down wood started to live there.  Many years ago, this land was given to a person who could farm it. It was probably used for raising animals and cutting down trees.

I chose this land because it is real. I looked at websites to see what kind of help the government gives to farmers.  I also looked at an organic farm near Potrero to see what a farmer could do there.

Culture is very important in any talk to try and agree. We can say culture is what it is not as much as what it really is. Culture is not the same for everyone. It is not one thing. Saying all Russians are stubborn or all Japanese are nice is wrong. It is better to understand how a culture works and how it will change a talk. When we meet a new culture, we see it in a way we understand from our own culture.

Trying to understand a new culture can mean learning about its history or its ideas. We should not judge or try to change a culture, we should just accept it. We need to work with it, especially when talking and trying to agree. If we are not strong in the talk, we need to be extra careful. If we are in a new place, showing respect for traditions can help us talk better.

Culture is not just about countries. Companies have their own cultures too. Some companies work long hours, others work more freely. We can see culture in how people dress, how they talk, and how they choose workers. Some companies like giving to charity, others only give to certain charities.

In America, companies are very different. Some are formal, others are casual. This shows how many different ways there are to think in one country. Some cultures seem the same on the outside, but we need to look deeper.

What is important to understand is why a culture does things. If a culture values saving face or being together, a person will not shame their company to win a talk. A person from a culture that likes to bargain hard will not give up easily. Before we talk and try to agree, we need to think about these things. But it is also good to learn about the other person so we can talk better.

The saying "The fool hath said in his heart, 'There is no God,'" comes from Psalm 14 in the Christian Bible. This saying begins St. Anselm's argument about God. Thomas Aquinas, another writer, also believes in God. Both men try to show that God exists. To compare them, we must assume they believe in the same God. 

Anselm says we can know God by looking inside ourselves. He thinks God exists in our minds. If we think about God, we know he must exist. This is like faith—believing in something without proof.

Aquinas says we can know God through reason and evidence, not just faith. He gives five reasons why God must exist. These reasons are like puzzle pieces. Each piece shows us a part of God, even if we can't see the whole picture. 


Both men make good points, but neither fully proves God exists.

Long ago, in the fifth or sixth century before Christ, a prince was born. This prince became known as Buddha. Buddha left his life of wealth and found peace. He taught people about how to live a good life. His teachings start the religion of Buddhism. One group called Theravada is the oldest.  Buddhism is very old, over two thousand five hundred years.  It is different today than when Buddha lived.

For example, in Sri Lanka, there is a yearly ceremony where people cut water. Monks and regular people take part.  This is a religious event, but Buddha never talked about it. 

Buddhism has changed over time.  Some changes are small, like the ceremony. Other changes are big, like how people understand Buddha's teachings. 

This change comes from many things. Some come from inside the Buddhist community, some come from outside. Some are good, some are bad.  

We will use some words a lot in this talk.

* **Inside:**  Something that comes from people inside Buddhism.
* **Outside:** Something that comes from people not in Buddhism.
* **Hostile:** Something that wants to hurt Buddhism.
* **Benign:** Something that does not want to hurt or help Buddhism.



First, let us talk about the basic ideas of Theravada Buddhism. Buddhists find peace in three things: Buddha, the teachings, and the community of Buddhists. The teachings are in a set of books called the Tripitaka. The first book is the Sutta Pitaka, which has the words of Buddha. The second is the Vinaya Pitaka, which has the rules for monks and nuns. The last is the Abhidhamma Pitaka, which has deeper ideas about Buddhism.

In Buddhism, there is no soul. Life is full of suffering. Everything changes.  These are big ideas. By understanding them, people can end the cycle of death and rebirth. They can also end their desires, anger, and confusion.  

The Vinaya Pitaka has rules for living a good life.  Regular people have five rules: do not kill, do not lie, do not steal, do not have sex outside of marriage, and do not drink alcohol. Monks and nuns have more rules.

The most important idea in Buddhism is the Four Noble Truths. First, life has suffering. Second, suffering comes from wanting things. Third, suffering can end. Fourth, there is a way to end suffering.

The United States and Mexico had a long time of trouble. This trouble went on for 57 years, from 1836 to 1893. (Diehl and Goerts 2000 p. 145).  The biggest time of trouble was the Mexican-American War of 1846-1848. The United States fought Mexico and won. The United States took Texas and the American Southwest. There were many other fights between the two countries. The fights stopped before World War I. 

The trouble started because Americans and Mexicans had different ideas about religion, culture, and how to live. They also wanted the same things. This is like other countries that share a border. Countries that are near each other often have problems. The United States and Mexico are like other countries that have had a long time of trouble. David M. Pletcher (1977) said, “Only in Mexico and Cuba can one find long-lasting American diplomatic problems” (p. 41). Both Mexico and Cuba are close to the United States and have had trouble with the United States. Other countries in Latin America have good relations with the United States.

Religion was a big problem between the two countries. This is a problem that has been around for a long time. Sally Frahm (2001) said, ”if in the twentieth century Americans were opposed to fascism and communism, in the eighteenth and nineteenth they were opposed to Catholicism and monarchy”  (p.86). Just like the Cold War between the United States and the Soviet Union, the trouble between the United States and Mexico was partly about ideas and partly about what each country wanted. But in this case, the ideas were about religion. The United States did not trust Mexico because it did not trust Spain. The people in the United States had heard bad things about Spain. This made it hard for the United States and Mexico to be friends.


Diehl and Goerts (2000) list 17 problems between Mexico and the United States. Most of the problems were about land. There were lots of fights between people from Mexico and the United States on the border. Bandits and bad people from American towns would go into Mexico and cause trouble. Both the United States and Mexico had to send soldiers to the border to stop this.

Schmitt (1974) said that the trouble between the two countries started to go away when Mexico became very dependent on the United States. The trouble ended when the United States wanted to control Mexico's economy.

Fifteen years ago I became sick. The illness came suddenly. I did not know it was going to happen.  I was a nurse then. I chose this job because I wanted safety. When I was young, people told me, "You can always be a nurse. People will always get sick." So I became a nurse, even though I wanted to be a scientist or a writer. 

When I got sick, I was 46 years old. I was single and did not have much money. I could not work. I am still sick today. I have lived on government help for 15 years. I have no money saved. I get by, but every day is hard. I worry about money, safety, and how people see me. I am not sure about the future. 

But I know one thing: I could not have survived without help from my family and friends. When bad things happen, you need people.

We all have problems in life, big and small. We can plan, but some things are too hard to face alone.

I agree that we should not depend only on the government. It is not working well. But I think we should help each other more. We should trust each other and ask for help when we need it. 

Some people say that Americans built this country by being independent. But the people who started this country did not succeed alone. They helped each other, respected each other, and shared what they had. The people who traveled west in covered wagons did not make it alone.

So, be prepared. I am. I have a kit with supplies for emergencies: first aid, water tablets, plastic sheeting, and tape. I have flashlights, batteries, candles, and matches. I have canned food. If you have land, grow your own food. It is a good idea to have a wood stove if you do not live in an apartment. 

But also, get to know your neighbors.

Why do living things change over time? Are there rules that show how they change? Even though a scientist named D’Arcy Thompson said in 1917 that we have not figured out how to use math to explain even simple life forms, we still say this today. In recent years, math has helped us understand how shells, or skeletons of sea creatures, grow and change over time. Our study looks at how math and experiments can show us how living things change over time. We used pictures of seashells to measure parts of them. We put these measurements into a computer program. We made new shell shapes to see what is possible. We want to use this with experiments to learn more about how shell shapes have changed over time.

A shell is like a tube that grows in a circle. It makes many loops called whorls. These whorls go around a line in the middle called the columella. The whorls can grow at different speeds. A line called a suture separates each whorl. The biggest whorl is the last one, called the body whorl. The top part of the shell, with all the whorls except the last one, is called the spire. The tip of the spire is called the apex.

We can look at a shell in different ways. The normal way is to see the opening, or aperture, of the shell.

To count the whorls, first look at the shell from the top. Then find the first suture. Draw a line to split the shell in half. Count the whorls from that line.

Think of a shell as a series of openings that move through space as the animal builds its shell. We can use math to follow the path of these openings. Once we have the math, we can change the shape of the shell.

Child and baby deaths in Indonesia have not gone down much in the last ten years. Indonesia is doing well at meeting many goals, like making sure people have clean water and toilets. But they are not doing well enough to meet the goals for health for mothers and children by 2015. We will talk about why this is.

Indonesia has more births with a doctor or nurse now, 72%. But this number includes midwives who can't do surgeries if a birth is hard. Many mothers die from bleeding after birth. So, this number is not good news.  Fewer children with diarrhea are getting help from a doctor. We do not have enough information about help after birth, but it is a problem.

Cesarean sections are not common in Indonesia, only 4%. This is low. In cities, 7% of babies are born this way. In the countryside, it is only 2%. This shows that people in the cities have better access to care. The poor have a much harder time getting care. They may not be able to pay.

What can be done to help? Should Indonesia make special programs or make the whole health system better? Special programs can be good because they target a specific problem. They can also show results quickly. But, they can also be bad.

If too much money goes to one program, other programs will not get enough money. People will want to work on the program with the most money. This happened with HIV/AIDS programs. They took money and people away from family planning.  Also, many programs can be the same. This makes things more complicated and costs more money.

Victorian books are known for being very detailed. They often talk about the rich people from that time. Two books that are from that time but are different are "Oliver Twist" and "Wuthering Heights". Both books have mystery and strange things in them. This is not common in books from that time. The mystery makes the characters feel more real. We understand them better.

One part from "Oliver Twist" shows this: 
"And now, hosts of bewildering and confusing ideas came crowding on his mind. He seemed to be still walking between Sikes and Crackit, who were angrily disputing: for the very words they said, sounded in his ears; and when he caught his own attention, … he found that he was talking to them…. Suddenly he started back at the report of fire arms; and there rose into the air loud cries and shouts; lights gleamed before his eyes, and all was noise and tumult, as some unseen hand bore him hurriedly away. Through all these rapid visions, there ran an undefined, uneasy consciousness of pain, which weared and tormented him incessantly.”
(Dickens, 220)

These books use mystery a lot in dreams or things that feel like dreams. But the dreams are different in each book. In "Oliver Twist", they show us what is happening inside Oliver. We see his pain and how he understands things around him.  When Oliver is shot, he remembers it like a dream. He is trying to find help (see left).
This shows that Oliver had no control over what happened. He was very sick. He has dreams of Sikes and Crackit. The shooting is very strong. All his senses are gone. He does not see the "unseen hand" that takes him away. He feels his pain over and over again, but it is different now. The pain is always there. He is scared. When Oliver is so overwhelmed, it makes us wonder who is responsible for his bad luck. It was not his fault. This shows that Oliver has no control over anything. He cannot even try to change things, even when his life is in danger. This part makes us think that Oliver is giving up. Maybe Fagin has broken him. He is making Oliver accept this sadness.

“The day passed off – day! There was no day; it was gone as soon as come – and night came on again; night so long, and yet so short; long in it’s dreadful silence and short in it’s fleeting ours.

A couple of years ago, I worked in an after school program. I helped students in grade school. I was best at helping with English and reading. One instructor asked me to help a boy named Adrian. He was in third or fourth grade and had trouble reading. 

Adrian was strange. He read some letters well, but others he got wrong. It was very odd. Adrian spoke English well. He was Latino, but he spoke perfect English. We had trouble helping him. 

One day, Adrian's mother came to the program. I was watching some other children while the rest went on a trip. Adrian's mother did not speak English. She only spoke Spanish. I knew some Spanish, but not much. We talked a little. Then it hit me. Adrian could read, but he did not know the English alphabet well. I do not know if this helped him much, but I hope he is doing better now.

I tell this story about Adrian to talk about the language barrier in schools. It is a big problem, especially in California. It is not always easy to see the problem.  Even if a child speaks English well, reading can be hard.

Everyone agrees this is a problem. So, what can we do? For Adrian, it was simple. We helped him with English reading and the alphabet. But for children who do not speak much English, the problem is harder. There is no one answer. We need to use many things: dual language programs, mainstream immersion, private tutors, and ESL classes. We need to use all of these things together.

First, dual language programs are a good idea. They are good for all children, not just those whose first language is Spanish. Studies show that children in these programs do better in school. Some people are afraid of these programs. They think they waste money and do not help most children. This is not true. If we used these programs in all schools, all children would benefit.

How can we do this? Do we need all teachers to be bilingual? No, this is not fair. But we can have bilingual aides or tutors.

Many people believe in something bigger than them. Some go to church or temple to learn about it. Some people take the beliefs of their parents. Other people do not believe. They think that life is all there is.  People change their beliefs over time.

Everyone looks for meaning in life. We want to find good things to help us through hard times.

My father liked cardinals. I asked him what his favorite bird was. We sat on our porch. It rained hard.

He looked out at the rain. He seemed sad. He was very thin. His hair was thin too.  He did not look at me. I felt afraid to talk to him about how much I would miss him.

I hugged him and sat closer. We watched the rain together.

My father died a few months later. He was sick for a long time. The medicine did not help much. I did not go to see him die. I did not want to watch him die. I wanted to remember him as he was when he was alive.

No one called me when he died.

The "Gothic Novel" is a new and old thing at the same time. This is what Ian Watt says in his book. The Gothic way of writing has been criticized and praised. Some say it is not deep, others say it is very powerful. The first Gothic Novel was called "The Castle of Otranto." It was written by Horace Walpole.  Walpole used old ideas from stories and new ideas from modern novels. He made a new kind of story.  He used old ideas from plays and new ideas from how nature looks. He called his story "A Gothic Story." The Gothic story often has things from old stories, buildings, and ways of life. Even when "The Castle of Otranto" was published, the word "Gothic" was used for many things. People thought it was old-fashioned. They thought modern things were better.  The Gothic story was new because it let the reader see the thoughts of the characters. This is why Gothic stories are still popular today.

One important idea in Gothic stories is knighthood. Knighthood was a way to train a knight in the old days. This idea is used in "The Castle of Otranto." Gothic writers liked to write about knighthood because it meant being brave, honorable, and good. They thought these things were missing in their time. 

Walpole wrote "The Castle of Otranto" during a time of trouble in his country. He thought things were getting bad. He may have thought that people in the past were better than people now. This idea is seen in a character named Frederic. The reader knows that Frederic is a good knight. He is a prince who has suffered. He is supposed to be dead.  The story makes him seem more than a real knight. This is a common thing in Gothic stories.

Supply chain management is how goods move.  It starts with a customer order and goes all the way to the customer.  It includes making the goods, getting the things needed to make them, and sending the goods to the customer. This term was first used in nineteen eighty-two by a man named Keith Oliver.  He said it was about planning, doing, and checking how the whole process works to make customers happy. 

There are six big parts to supply chain management: making the goods, getting the supplies, keeping track of what's in stock, choosing where to make and sell things, moving the goods, and sharing information.  Managers use these parts to give good service to customers.

Making the goods is the first step. This is very important. Managers need to know what customers want. They look at the market to see what people are buying. Once they know what people want, they decide what to make and how much. They also decide where to make the goods and which factory is best.  They need to make sure the goods are good and that customers are happy.

The next part is getting the things needed to make the goods. This means choosing the best factories or companies to work with. Sometimes companies share work with other companies to make things faster and cheaper.

A sign says that Hitler is alive in Burma. 

Ellen Page, star of the movie "Juno," stands alone on a street corner. She holds a piece of cardboard above her head. The sign has a message written on it with a marker. The message is strange. Burma, also known as Myanmar, is a country in Southeast Asia. It is ruled by a mean group of leaders. This group took over the country in 1962. In 2007, many people in Burma protested in the streets. These were the first protests in ten years. The protests were led by Buddhist monks. The monks wore yellow robes, so people called them "The Saffron Revolution." At first, the government let the monks have peaceful gatherings. But then the protests became more violent. The army attacked the monks and took over many monasteries. Reporters from other countries were arrested. A Japanese reporter named Kenji Nagai was killed on September 27, 2007. He was just at a protest. The government says 13 people died. But a soldier who left the army said many more people were killed.

This is not new. Governments have always tried to stop people from disagreeing with them. This has happened since the beginning of history. Old Roman leaders said they were chosen by gods to rule. Some people in Japan believe their emperor is a god.

Some people remember protests in China in 1989. People gathered at Tiananmen Square to protest the government. The government says 200-300 people died. But other groups say 2,000-3,000 people died. Another example is the genocide in Rwanda in the 1990s. Hutu groups killed many Tutsis. They also killed people who did not agree with them. Hitler and the Nazi party killed many Jewish people.

Duke Ellington make great jazz music for a long time. 

He good at making music that show off his band.  He play piano, but he good at writing music too. His music is full of sound and color.

Ellington make music where singers and players can sing and play free. He also write music that is tight and good.

He know how to make each player sound good. He make the whole orchestra sound good too. This make his music very special.

One book about music say Ellington use voice like an instrument. 

He do this in a song called Creole Love Call. This song is slow. It use voice and woodwinds.

The voice start smooth, then get rough. A trumpet play a solo. A clarinet play a high solo.

The band play together. The voice get high and rough.

Ellington use voice like an instrument in many songs. 

In Hot and Bothered, Ellington use trumpet and voice. It sound good together.

In It Don’t Mean a Thing, Ellington use trombone to start a song.

She always felt she needed some thing. It was a want that would not go away. It started when she was about fourteen, a young teenager.  The want was still there three years later when she was seventeen. Now, she knew she wanted a person, not a thing. But she felt no interest in boys. Some boys liked her and tried to be nice, but no one was good enough. She often thought about this strange thing. She tried to think why she did not want a boyfriend. She thought about it for years, but she did not have a good answer. So she lived her life, always thinking about her wants.

Her days at home were usually calm. Her parents were good people. They never argued. They rarely argued with her, too. The only time they argued was when she said she wanted to do things her way. She was the daughter of calm people, but she had a big, fun personality. She was nice, so people liked her.

Today was not a calm day. She walked around the house, looking for something to do. She heard a short scream from the kitchen. She ran to the kitchen and saw her mother on the floor. Her mother was in pain and said "Ow" over and over. Her daughter ran to her side and asked, "Mom! Mom, what is wrong?"

"Ouch...sweetheart, I need you to take me to the hospital," her mother said. Her words were short and fast. Her daughter knew she was in a lot of pain. "Okay, Mom. Just tell me where to pick you up." Her mother pointed with her hand. The daughter was happy she had taken classes to make herself strong. She carried her mother to the car, put her in the back, and drove to the hospital.

The hospital smelled like cleaning supplies and sickness. But she was not scared. She was too worried about her mother. She carried her mother inside and called for a doctor. Some doctors came and put her mother on a bed. They took her mother to see a doctor. The daughter sat and waited.

Her mother had fallen off a step stool while she was trying to get a vase from a high shelf.

This study looked at if eating a "Mediterranean Diet" (Med diet) helps keep people's hearts healthy.  People who ate a lot of Med diet foods had a lower chance of getting heart disease and stroke.  The Med diet has lots of good things like fruits, nuts, and fish. 

Before, studies showed that the Med diet helps people live longer and have less heart problems. But no one looked at if it helps with stroke.

This study followed 74,886 women for 20 years. The women told the doctors what they ate every few years.  The doctors checked if these women got heart disease or stroke.  They also looked at things like if the women smoked, took medicine, or were active. 

The doctors found that women who ate more Med diet foods had a lower chance of getting heart disease and stroke.

In two thousand seven, the United States had a big money problem. People lost jobs, homes cost less, and many big companies had much trouble. This problem is still here. We must ask: how did this happen? How can we stop it?

The problem was big decisions made by people who only cared about money. They told banks to give loans to people who could not pay. This happened because the system for giving loans was not strong enough.  Also, two groups, Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, took these bad loans and made them into new things called CDOs and CDSs. When people could not pay back their loans, the banks had no money. They gave the problem to the new things they made. This hurt the whole country.

The problem started in nineteen ninety-nine when President Clinton wanted to be president again. He wanted to be popular so he made it easy for people to get loans. Steven Holmes, who writes for the New York Times, said in nineteen ninety-nine that this could be bad. He said that Fannie Mae, a big company that helps people get loans, might have problems. He said it could be like the problem with banks in the nineteen eighties. Holmes was right.

Many things made the problem worse. New kinds of loans were made, and these loans were complicated. People borrowed too much money to buy homes. When home prices went down, many people could not pay. Companies that had bought these loans lost a lot of money.

The five biggest companies that help people invest money had a lot of money tied up in loans. In two thousand seven, they lost a lot of money. Some companies had to sell themselves cheaply. One company was split up. And two other big companies had to change the way they worked. Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac also had many bad loans and had to be controlled by the government.

Ah, exposition. That is the part of a story where a writer shows their skills. It can be amazing or terrible. Too much exposition can make readers bored and put the story to sleep. 

Exposition is when the writer tells the reader what happened. It is like a character in a movie giving a long speech. In a story, the author does the telling.

For example, imagine a story where a hero meets his love. We are told they met at a special place and time, got married in a big way, and then the husband was killed. A good writer would not spend two pages telling us all this. Instead, they would show us the hero's love for his wife through his words and actions.  We would see how much his wife loved him and how he changed her life. This would make us care about him more and feel sad when he dies.

Good writing needs to show us the story, not just tell us about it.  When we want to know about a new character, like someone who used to be in the Air Force and now works at a gas station, we want to learn about them through their actions and words. Show us their dreams, their fears, and their everyday life.

I look at two news shows from Columbus, Ohio. The first was NBC 4 this morning (August 13, 2011). It was live. The main story was about a man in Ashley, Ohio. He hurt his wife.  Her name was not said, but his name was Shad Hostettler. They showed his picture. He looked bad. They talked about this story for two minutes. They said he hurt his wife many times and was arrested. I think they talked about it for the right amount of time. 

The next story was about a man named Travis Buyers. He was 18 years old. He was shot in the morning in Sharon Woods. He was hurt badly. No one had been arrested. The SWAT team was looking into it. This story was short. I think this is because he was a black man or lived in a black neighborhood. I have seen this before. The news does not talk much about crimes against black people. White people are talked about more.

The next story was about a hole in a helicopter.  The hole was from a gun. They said it was a small bullet from a gun. They gave money to help find the person who shot the helicopter.

Then they talked about the rain coming on Saturday. They said the weather would be warm. They did not talk about it for long. They wanted to make you watch more.

They also talked about a robbery at a store in Columbus. A black man robbed the store. He was tall and thin. They said he was black a lot.

The last story was about a man named Rene Rodriguez. He was from Texas. He sold a lot of drugs in Ohio. He went to prison for a long time. They said he was Hispanic. This did not seem important.

Brothers have a strong bond. This bond is very important. It has many feelings: love, pride, jealousy, and anger. Brothers know each other very well. They see themselves in their brother.

This bond is most strong when things are bad. The true nature of the bond shows. It can be good or bad. These feelings have a big cost.

To understand the feelings between brothers, we must see the results. When you look at your brother, you see yourself. You see yourself as you truly are. Your actions and the results show your real character.

In "The Scarlet Ibis", two brothers show this theme. They have many strong feelings.  

In a beautiful place, the brothers go on a journey. They fail. At the end, there is sadness and pride. One brother lives.

The story shows the feelings of the main character, Doodle. It shows how he feels about his brother. The story also shows how the main character sees the world. These things affect his actions.

The main character feels pride. From the time he and Doodle go out together, he feels sad about Doodle. He wanted a brother to teach. He wanted a brother to play with. Doodle is sick and cannot do these things. 

The main character is angry at Doodle. He thinks about hurting Doodle. But he sees Doodle smile, and he feels love.

The brain is very complex. It is good at thinking and making new things. As technology got better, people used new words to talk about the brain. First they said it was like a tablet, then like paper, then like a book, and now like a computer. But these words are not perfect. They can make people think wrong things.

The brain takes in information from our senses. Our senses feel things like touch, heat, sound, and light. The brain turns these feelings into signals. The brain uses these signals to understand the world.

When we see a black box on a white background, the brain looks at the colors, shapes, and edges. This helps us see the box. The brain also uses what it already knows to help us see the box. For example, it knows that boxes are usually solid, not holes.

The brain also pays attention to important things. It looks at everything, but it focuses on what is important. We might not notice each blade of grass, but we notice our name when someone says it.

The brain stores information in different ways. Some information is short-term, like when we remember a phone number for a few seconds. Other information is long-term, like our name and birthday. The brain stores information in different parts and uses it later.

There are many ways to learn about how the brain works. Some people study how people remember things. Others study computers. Others study the brain itself. One idea is that the brain stores information like a network of ideas. Each idea is connected to other ideas. For example, the idea of "chair" is connected to the idea of "table" and "wood".

Aldous Huxley writes about a bad future. In his book, "Brave New World," people are happy but not free. They live in a world where the government controls everything. People are taught to be happy and not care about others. They do not think for themselves.  They only want to have fun.

Huxley is worried about new technology and how it can be used to control people. He also worries about how money can be used to control people. He uses his book to show how bad these things can be.  

The book shows how people can be tricked into being happy even if they are not free. The people in the book do not know that they are being controlled. They think they are happy, but they are not.

Huxley uses ideas from Karl Marx to show how bad this future could be. Marx believed that rich people control poor people by making them think that they are happy. This is called "false consciousness."

In "Brave New World," the government controls the people by making them watch television and buy things. The people are happy because they are distracted by these things. They do not think about the fact that they are being controlled.

I go to school at University Park for two and a half years. I live in a dorm. It is far from the center of campus. Walking to class can take a long time, maybe twenty five minutes. I talk to a school alum. They said that the area near my dorm used to be empty. Now it has new buildings. The campus is getting bigger. It is hard to get around.

What is the best way to get around? A bike is good. But the campus needs to be good for bikes.

My friend just started riding a bike again. He said bikes are good.

Bikes are good for your body. They are also fast. A small meal and some exercise can take you far.

I live off campus. It is far from the center. I bought a bike.

It takes twenty five minutes to walk to my class. On a bike, it takes five minutes.

But the road is not good for bikes. I like to walk, but I am busy. Without a bike, I would walk. Walking to class every day takes a long time.

I do not have that time.

In pursuing an education in social work, I intend to follow a career path with the Division of Family and Children Services to help children who have been abused or neglected; and to provide support for troubled families. Values that I can provide to the social work field include the following: service, respect, ethical nature, commitment to help improve relationships between others and to improve myself professionally to remain competent in my field. These core values are not just important to social workers; they are important to me personally. 

	I have always wanted to help others, but I was unsure of the career path that I wanted to follow. Throughout my years in high school and college, I saw many individuals flee from their problems in denial and a few used coping mechanisms that were less than ideal. Because of situations that I have witnessed, I chose to pursue a Bachelor’s degree in Psychology. Still unsure of a career path, I decided to take a break once I graduated from Piedmont College in 2009. One day that summer, I visited a friend who introduced me to a sixteen year-old boy sitting nervously on her couch. She explained to me why he was visiting: to escape his abusive parents. The next day, I learned that he had called the police to his parent’s residence. To see if I could help in any way, I drove over to his parents’ house. Once there, I privately explained my concerns to the police and told them I had just graduated with a degree in Psychology from Piedmont College. The police requested that I talk to the parents since there was nothing that the law could do for the teenager. When I questioned the parents about the situation, they seemed nervous and used excuses to describe their son’s “manipulative” behavior for involving outside sources to resolve “simple” disputes. After this particular experience, I began to seriously consider a career in social work to help children with “simple” disputes among family members.

	Another value that is important for the field of social work is social justice. As a society, we claim that the individual is important and we mourn those that we have lost. The concept of the “individual” that society holds is more a follower of archaic traditions than actual uniqueness. So, if society mourns lost individuals, then why do we strive to be similar to “everyone else?” I am an individual and do not enjoy placing limitations on myself to be similar to others. Throughout my years at high school and college, I protested against social injustice whenever I could: coloring my hair unnatural colors, wearing clothing that fit my personality, piercing my ears past the traditional set, declaring my involvement with GSBA (Gay Straight Bisexual Alliance), fighting against both racism and discrimination whenever I witnessed it, etc. I believe in social justice and I will continue to protest against social injustice.

The following paper addresses the Biological and Sociocultural models in relation to the disorder insomnia. The biological model focuses on genetic information that is inherited as well as medical aspects of health. The Sociocultural models look at environmental relationships and their applications to race, ethnicity, demographics, and socioeconomic status. The following review of insomnia looks at these models and explains each piece of research chosen to relate to and to better explain the models. The explanations of the research and their findings are then critiqued to mention their specific strengths and weaknesses.

A sleep disorder can be characterized as a primary sleep disorder, a sleep disorder related to another mental disorder, or a sleep disorder related to other issues. The Primary sleep disorders are Dyssonmias or Parasomnias while sleep disorders related to another mental disorder are related to an Axis I or Axis II disorder. Other categories of sleep disorders can be due to medical complications or the intake of a substance. The Dyssomnias are: Primary Insomnia, Primary Hypersomnia, Narcolepsy, Breathing- Related Sleep Disorder, Circadian Rhythm Sleep Disorder, and Dyssomnia Not Otherwise Specified (NOS). While Primary Insomnia is a complication in adequate or maintained sleep, Primary Hypersomnia is a difficulty in staying awake, both for at least a one month period of time. Narcolepsy involves cataplexy and/ or automatic REM. While Dyssonmias focus on initiating and remaining asleep, the Parasomnias are sleep disorders associated with behavioral abnormalities and/ or physiological occurrences. Parasomnias are Nightmare Disorder, Sleep Terror Disorder, Sleepwalking Disorder, and Parasomnias Not Otherwise Specified. The sleep disorders related to another mental disorder involve sleep difficulties due to Axis I (Clinical Disorders) or Axis II (Personality Disorders or Mental Retardation). The following review focuses on insomnia, and somewhat on primary sleep disorders in general in relation to the biological and sociocultural models.

	 The biological model of sleep disorders focuses on genes, heritable factors, and physiologically acquired aspect of sleep disorders. Neurons in the hypothalamus containing orexin are responsible for the regulation of sleep and wakefulness. This study experimented with mice and found that there are phenotypic GABAB receptors on the orexin neurons which are specifically responsible for sleep/ wake states. The activation of the GABAA receptor induces responses that promote sleep. If it is inhibited from firing, this can cause reduced anxiety and induce sleep. The GABAB agonist (baclofen) increased sleep time (Matsuki et al., 2009). Such results imply that the animal models of mice can be generalized to studies in humans. This shows that there is a genetic and environmental basis for the physical GABAB receptor in humans. A problem or absence with this receptor could alter the ability of one to have adequate sleep without medication. The sociocultural implication of this study is that if the phenotype was inherited, this could regulate sleep, and an alteration of the receptor would naturally disturb sleep for an individual. This would negatively impact aspects of life such as school, career, and every day events that involve monotonous tasks and focus.

This paper covers three areas of Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD). First, a brief definition of the disorder is provided. Next, diagnosis is explained, with common characteristics, or “red flags”. Finally, the paper concludes with ways that a teacher in a mainstreamed classroom environment can assist a student with CAPD.

	Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD), or Auditory Processing Disorder (APD) “refers to the efficiency and effectiveness by which the central nervous system (CNS) utilizes auditory information. Narrowly defined, (C)AP refers to the perceptual processing of auditory information in the CNS and the neurobiologic activity that underlies that processing and gives rise to electrophysiologic auditory potentials” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005), meaning it is a disorder wherein the central nervous system (i.e. the brain) cannot properly process things that are heard. People with CAPD can hear normally, and are therefore not considered “hearing impaired”; rather, the area of the brain that translates what we hear, separating words or differentiating conversation from background noise does not function as it typically should. 

	The earliest mention of the disorder that became CAPD is from the mid-1950s, called “auditory imperception” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005) when researchers were evaluating children with communicative disorders. The Italian research team of Bocca, Calearo, and Cassinari began developing tests for these children in 1954; in 1961, Kimura “introduced dichotic testing and formulated a model to explain the physiology of the CANS underlying dichotic perception” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005). A national conference was held in 1977 that stimulated research on children with CAPD. 

	CAPD manifests itself in multiple ways: the person suffering may not be able to localize or hear sound in space; may have difficulty discriminating between two or more “acoustic events” (sound occurrences); may not be able to recognize sound patterns; may not be able to differentiate changes in speech (like detecting sarcasm based on change of voice); one sound may be blocked by a subsequent sound; may not have the ability to synthesize sound clues (that is, interpret in a meaningful way that they can then act upon); and may not be able to determine the sequence in which auditory information is presented (Ferre).

	In order to diagnose CAPD, the patient must be screened with “systematic observation of listening behavior and/or performance on tests of auditory function”, which may be conducted by “audiologists, SLPs, psychologists, and others using a variety of measures that evaluate auditory-related skills” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005). This may include questionnaires and surveys, observation of auditory behaviors, including how the patient responds to certain stimuli. There is, at this time, no one tool or test that is used consistently to a high rate of diagnostic success, and there is no known cause for the disorder. Many tests used present the patient with multiple, simultaneous auditory stimuli and then ask for them to differentiate certain items, like a series of words or numbers. More advanced tests include recording acoustic signals within the ear and measuring the responses to the signals.

The play Twelfth Night seems to say that although disguise is in fact useful in perpetrating long bouts of deception, in the end a person must reject that newly formed guise, or else risk losing themselves forever in the process. A big problem with ending a deception, however, is that one may find themselves alienated in the process. Therefore, in the end, one must decide between one’s own self preservation, or the preservation of relationships with those around them. For although some will respond neutrally to discovering that they’ve been tricked, still others will not take the deception so lightly, and will be likely be offended by the whole charade.
The topic of deception in gender role reversal is especially problematic, because it brings up many side issues, perhaps the most important one being, why? Why does the subject feel the need to shirk their own identity and take up a disguise in the form of the opposite gender? In Viola’s case, it is obviously a form of self protection.: “I’ll bring you to a captain in this town/ Where lie my maiden weeds, by whose gentle help/ I was preserved to serve this noble count…” (5.1.247-249)
Having newly arrived in a foreign land, Viola feels it necessary to pretend to be a man to protect herself from would be attackers. Viola’s plan works, but it also alienates her from the women around her, cutting her off from an important support system. To make matters worse, she is apparently so convincing at appearing to be a man that Olivia confuses her with Sebastian, and in effect falls in love with her. “Whither, my lord? Cesario, husband, stay.” (5.1.138) On top of that, she also has to deal with suppressed romantic desires between her and Orsino: “Boy, thou hast said to me a thousand times/ Thou never shouldst love woman like to me.” (5.1. 260-261)
Although this may be a somewhat progressive attitude, to the modern reader, Twelfth Night may be seen as an illustration of how deception may help facilitate the unveiling of suppressed emotions, especially in the cases of Olivia and Orsino. Certain passages seem to hint that the aforesaid characters may have unexpressed subconscious desires that the appearance of Viola/Cesario forces them to deal with. For instance, is Olivia attracted to Cesario because Cesario appears to be a man, or does Olivia really secretly harbor feelings for women? One would argue that this is probably not the case, because Shakespeare’s character Olivia seems more likely to be parodying those people of his time period who judge others only upon their looks. 
This is evidenced by the ease with which Olivia switches her romantic ardors from Cesario to Sebastian, and begins to regard Cesario/Viola as family rather than a love interest: “A sister, you are she.” (5.1.315)

German colonial rule has been noted by various observers for its brutality, notably with respect to the genocide of the Ovaherero and Nama in German South West Africa. Of course nothing so broad as an entire colonial empire can be accounted for by such a simple description. The German colonial empire was as varied in policies and ruling style as it was in geography. Educational provision across the colonies was similarly diverse.
