When I got sick, I was 46 years old. I was single and did not have much money. I could not work. I am still sick today. I have lived on government help for 15 years. I have no money saved. I get by, but every day is hard. I worry about money, safety, and how people see me. I am not sure about the future. 

But I know one thing: I could not have survived without help from my family and friends. When bad things happen, you need people.

We all have problems in life, big and small. We can plan, but some things are too hard to face alone.

I agree that we should not depend only on the government. It is not working well. But I think we should help each other more. We should trust each other and ask for help when we need it. 

Some people say that Americans built this country by being independent. But the people who started this country did not succeed alone. They helped each other, respected each other, and shared what they had. The people who traveled west in covered wagons did not make it alone.

So, be prepared. I am. I have a kit with supplies for emergencies: first aid, water tablets, plastic sheeting, and tape. I have flashlights, batteries, candles, and matches. I have canned food. If you have land, grow your own food. It is a good idea to have a wood stove if you do not live in an apartment. 

But also, get to know your neighbors.

Why do living things change over time? Are there rules that show how they change? Even though a scientist named D’Arcy Thompson said in 1917 that we have not figured out how to use math to explain even simple life forms, we still say this today. In recent years, math has helped us understand how shells, or skeletons of sea creatures, grow and change over time. Our study looks at how math and experiments can show us how living things change over time. We used pictures of seashells to measure parts of them. We put these measurements into a computer program. We made new shell shapes to see what is possible. We want to use this with experiments to learn more about how shell shapes have changed over time.

A shell is like a tube that grows in a circle. It makes many loops called whorls. These whorls go around a line in the middle called the columella. The whorls can grow at different speeds. A line called a suture separates each whorl. The biggest whorl is the last one, called the body whorl. The top part of the shell, with all the whorls except the last one, is called the spire. The tip of the spire is called the apex.

We can look at a shell in different ways. The normal way is to see the opening, or aperture, of the shell.

To count the whorls, first look at the shell from the top. Then find the first suture. Draw a line to split the shell in half. Count the whorls from that line.

Think of a shell as a series of openings that move through space as the animal builds its shell. We can use math to follow the path of these openings. Once we have the math, we can change the shape of the shell.

Child and baby deaths in Indonesia have not gone down much in the last ten years. Indonesia is doing well at meeting many goals, like making sure people have clean water and toilets. But they are not doing well enough to meet the goals for health for mothers and children by 2015. We will talk about why this is.

Indonesia has more births with a doctor or nurse now, 72%. But this number includes midwives who can't do surgeries if a birth is hard. Many mothers die from bleeding after birth. So, this number is not good news.  Fewer children with diarrhea are getting help from a doctor. We do not have enough information about help after birth, but it is a problem.

Cesarean sections are not common in Indonesia, only 4%. This is low. In cities, 7% of babies are born this way. In the countryside, it is only 2%. This shows that people in the cities have better access to care. The poor have a much harder time getting care. They may not be able to pay.

What can be done to help? Should Indonesia make special programs or make the whole health system better? Special programs can be good because they target a specific problem. They can also show results quickly. But, they can also be bad.

If too much money goes to one program, other programs will not get enough money. People will want to work on the program with the most money. This happened with HIV/AIDS programs. They took money and people away from family planning.  Also, many programs can be the same. This makes things more complicated and costs more money.

Victorian books are known for being very detailed. They often talk about the rich people from that time. Two books that are from that time but are different are "Oliver Twist" and "Wuthering Heights". Both books have mystery and strange things in them. This is not common in books from that time. The mystery makes the characters feel more real. We understand them better.

One part from "Oliver Twist" shows this: 
"And now, hosts of bewildering and confusing ideas came crowding on his mind. He seemed to be still walking between Sikes and Crackit, who were angrily disputing: for the very words they said, sounded in his ears; and when he caught his own attention, … he found that he was talking to them…. Suddenly he started back at the report of fire arms; and there rose into the air loud cries and shouts; lights gleamed before his eyes, and all was noise and tumult, as some unseen hand bore him hurriedly away. Through all these rapid visions, there ran an undefined, uneasy consciousness of pain, which weared and tormented him incessantly.”
(Dickens, 220)

These books use mystery a lot in dreams or things that feel like dreams. But the dreams are different in each book. In "Oliver Twist", they show us what is happening inside Oliver. We see his pain and how he understands things around him.  When Oliver is shot, he remembers it like a dream. He is trying to find help (see left).
This shows that Oliver had no control over what happened. He was very sick. He has dreams of Sikes and Crackit. The shooting is very strong. All his senses are gone. He does not see the "unseen hand" that takes him away. He feels his pain over and over again, but it is different now. The pain is always there. He is scared. When Oliver is so overwhelmed, it makes us wonder who is responsible for his bad luck. It was not his fault. This shows that Oliver has no control over anything. He cannot even try to change things, even when his life is in danger. This part makes us think that Oliver is giving up. Maybe Fagin has broken him. He is making Oliver accept this sadness.

A couple of years ago, I worked in an after school program. I helped students in grade school. I was best at helping with English and reading. One instructor asked me to help a boy named Adrian. He was in third or fourth grade and had trouble reading. 

Adrian was strange. He read some letters well, but others he got wrong. It was very odd. Adrian spoke English well. He was Latino, but he spoke perfect English. We had trouble helping him. 

One day, Adrian's mother came to the program. I was watching some other children while the rest went on a trip. Adrian's mother did not speak English. She only spoke Spanish. I knew some Spanish, but not much. We talked a little. Then it hit me. Adrian could read, but he did not know the English alphabet well. I do not know if this helped him much, but I hope he is doing better now.

I tell this story about Adrian to talk about the language barrier in schools. It is a big problem, especially in California. It is not always easy to see the problem.  Even if a child speaks English well, reading can be hard.

Everyone agrees this is a problem. So, what can we do? For Adrian, it was simple. We helped him with English reading and the alphabet. But for children who do not speak much English, the problem is harder. There is no one answer. We need to use many things: dual language programs, mainstream immersion, private tutors, and ESL classes. We need to use all of these things together.

First, dual language programs are a good idea. They are good for all children, not just those whose first language is Spanish. Studies show that children in these programs do better in school. Some people are afraid of these programs. They think they waste money and do not help most children. This is not true. If we used these programs in all schools, all children would benefit.

How can we do this? Do we need all teachers to be bilingual? No, this is not fair. But we can have bilingual aides or tutors.

Many people believe in something bigger than them. Some go to church or temple to learn about it. Some people take the beliefs of their parents. Other people do not believe. They think that life is all there is.  People change their beliefs over time.

Everyone looks for meaning in life. We want to find good things to help us through hard times.

My father liked cardinals. I asked him what his favorite bird was. We sat on our porch. It rained hard.

He looked out at the rain. He seemed sad. He was very thin. His hair was thin too.  He did not look at me. I felt afraid to talk to him about how much I would miss him.

I hugged him and sat closer. We watched the rain together.

My father died a few months later. He was sick for a long time. The medicine did not help much. I did not go to see him die. I did not want to watch him die. I wanted to remember him as he was when he was alive.

No one called me when he died.

The "Gothic Novel" is a new and old thing at the same time. This is what Ian Watt says in his book. The Gothic way of writing has been criticized and praised. Some say it is not deep, others say it is very powerful. The first Gothic Novel was called "The Castle of Otranto." It was written by Horace Walpole.  Walpole used old ideas from stories and new ideas from modern novels. He made a new kind of story.  He used old ideas from plays and new ideas from how nature looks. He called his story "A Gothic Story." The Gothic story often has things from old stories, buildings, and ways of life. Even when "The Castle of Otranto" was published, the word "Gothic" was used for many things. People thought it was old-fashioned. They thought modern things were better.  The Gothic story was new because it let the reader see the thoughts of the characters. This is why Gothic stories are still popular today.

One important idea in Gothic stories is knighthood. Knighthood was a way to train a knight in the old days. This idea is used in "The Castle of Otranto." Gothic writers liked to write about knighthood because it meant being brave, honorable, and good. They thought these things were missing in their time. 

Walpole wrote "The Castle of Otranto" during a time of trouble in his country. He thought things were getting bad. He may have thought that people in the past were better than people now. This idea is seen in a character named Frederic. The reader knows that Frederic is a good knight. He is a prince who has suffered. He is supposed to be dead.  The story makes him seem more than a real knight. This is a common thing in Gothic stories.

Supply chain management is how goods move.  It starts with a customer order and goes all the way to the customer.  It includes making the goods, getting the things needed to make them, and sending the goods to the customer. This term was first used in nineteen eighty-two by a man named Keith Oliver.  He said it was about planning, doing, and checking how the whole process works to make customers happy. 

There are six big parts to supply chain management: making the goods, getting the supplies, keeping track of what's in stock, choosing where to make and sell things, moving the goods, and sharing information.  Managers use these parts to give good service to customers.

Making the goods is the first step. This is very important. Managers need to know what customers want. They look at the market to see what people are buying. Once they know what people want, they decide what to make and how much. They also decide where to make the goods and which factory is best.  They need to make sure the goods are good and that customers are happy.

The next part is getting the things needed to make the goods. This means choosing the best factories or companies to work with. Sometimes companies share work with other companies to make things faster and cheaper.

A sign says that Hitler is alive in Burma. 

Ellen Page, star of the movie "Juno," stands alone on a street corner. She holds a piece of cardboard above her head. The sign has a message written on it with a marker. The message is strange. Burma, also known as Myanmar, is a country in Southeast Asia. It is ruled by a mean group of leaders. This group took over the country in 1962. In 2007, many people in Burma protested in the streets. These were the first protests in ten years. The protests were led by Buddhist monks. The monks wore yellow robes, so people called them "The Saffron Revolution." At first, the government let the monks have peaceful gatherings. But then the protests became more violent. The army attacked the monks and took over many monasteries. Reporters from other countries were arrested. A Japanese reporter named Kenji Nagai was killed on September 27, 2007. He was just at a protest. The government says 13 people died. But a soldier who left the army said many more people were killed.

This is not new. Governments have always tried to stop people from disagreeing with them. This has happened since the beginning of history. Old Roman leaders said they were chosen by gods to rule. Some people in Japan believe their emperor is a god.

Some people remember protests in China in 1989. People gathered at Tiananmen Square to protest the government. The government says 200-300 people died. But other groups say 2,000-3,000 people died. Another example is the genocide in Rwanda in the 1990s. Hutu groups killed many Tutsis. They also killed people who did not agree with them. Hitler and the Nazi party killed many Jewish people.

Duke Ellington make great jazz music for a long time. 

He good at making music that show off his band.  He play piano, but he good at writing music too. His music is full of sound and color.

Ellington make music where singers and players can sing and play free. He also write music that is tight and good.

He know how to make each player sound good. He make the whole orchestra sound good too. This make his music very special.

One book about music say Ellington use voice like an instrument. 

He do this in a song called Creole Love Call. This song is slow. It use voice and woodwinds.

The voice start smooth, then get rough. A trumpet play a solo. A clarinet play a high solo.

The band play together. The voice get high and rough.

Ellington use voice like an instrument in many songs. 

In Hot and Bothered, Ellington use trumpet and voice. It sound good together.

In It Don’t Mean a Thing, Ellington use trombone to start a song.

She always felt she needed some thing. It was a want that would not go away. It started when she was about fourteen, a young teenager.  The want was still there three years later when she was seventeen. Now, she knew she wanted a person, not a thing. But she felt no interest in boys. Some boys liked her and tried to be nice, but no one was good enough. She often thought about this strange thing. She tried to think why she did not want a boyfriend. She thought about it for years, but she did not have a good answer. So she lived her life, always thinking about her wants.

Her days at home were usually calm. Her parents were good people. They never argued. They rarely argued with her, too. The only time they argued was when she said she wanted to do things her way. She was the daughter of calm people, but she had a big, fun personality. She was nice, so people liked her.

Today was not a calm day. She walked around the house, looking for something to do. She heard a short scream from the kitchen. She ran to the kitchen and saw her mother on the floor. Her mother was in pain and said "Ow" over and over. Her daughter ran to her side and asked, "Mom! Mom, what is wrong?"

"Ouch...sweetheart, I need you to take me to the hospital," her mother said. Her words were short and fast. Her daughter knew she was in a lot of pain. "Okay, Mom. Just tell me where to pick you up." Her mother pointed with her hand. The daughter was happy she had taken classes to make herself strong. She carried her mother to the car, put her in the back, and drove to the hospital.

The hospital smelled like cleaning supplies and sickness. But she was not scared. She was too worried about her mother. She carried her mother inside and called for a doctor. Some doctors came and put her mother on a bed. They took her mother to see a doctor. The daughter sat and waited.

Her mother had fallen off a step stool while she was trying to get a vase from a high shelf.

This study looked at if eating a "Mediterranean Diet" (Med diet) helps keep people's hearts healthy.  People who ate a lot of Med diet foods had a lower chance of getting heart disease and stroke.  The Med diet has lots of good things like fruits, nuts, and fish. 

Before, studies showed that the Med diet helps people live longer and have less heart problems. But no one looked at if it helps with stroke.

This study followed 74,886 women for 20 years. The women told the doctors what they ate every few years.  The doctors checked if these women got heart disease or stroke.  They also looked at things like if the women smoked, took medicine, or were active. 

The doctors found that women who ate more Med diet foods had a lower chance of getting heart disease and stroke.

In two thousand seven, the United States had a big money problem. People lost jobs, homes cost less, and many big companies had much trouble. This problem is still here. We must ask: how did this happen? How can we stop it?

The problem was big decisions made by people who only cared about money. They told banks to give loans to people who could not pay. This happened because the system for giving loans was not strong enough.  Also, two groups, Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, took these bad loans and made them into new things called CDOs and CDSs. When people could not pay back their loans, the banks had no money. They gave the problem to the new things they made. This hurt the whole country.

The problem started in nineteen ninety-nine when President Clinton wanted to be president again. He wanted to be popular so he made it easy for people to get loans. Steven Holmes, who writes for the New York Times, said in nineteen ninety-nine that this could be bad. He said that Fannie Mae, a big company that helps people get loans, might have problems. He said it could be like the problem with banks in the nineteen eighties. Holmes was right.

Many things made the problem worse. New kinds of loans were made, and these loans were complicated. People borrowed too much money to buy homes. When home prices went down, many people could not pay. Companies that had bought these loans lost a lot of money.

The five biggest companies that help people invest money had a lot of money tied up in loans. In two thousand seven, they lost a lot of money. Some companies had to sell themselves cheaply. One company was split up. And two other big companies had to change the way they worked. Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac also had many bad loans and had to be controlled by the government.

Ah, exposition. That is the part of a story where a writer shows their skills. It can be amazing or terrible. Too much exposition can make readers bored and put the story to sleep. 

Exposition is when the writer tells the reader what happened. It is like a character in a movie giving a long speech. In a story, the author does the telling.

For example, imagine a story where a hero meets his love. We are told they met at a special place and time, got married in a big way, and then the husband was killed. A good writer would not spend two pages telling us all this. Instead, they would show us the hero's love for his wife through his words and actions.  We would see how much his wife loved him and how he changed her life. This would make us care about him more and feel sad when he dies.

Good writing needs to show us the story, not just tell us about it.  When we want to know about a new character, like someone who used to be in the Air Force and now works at a gas station, we want to learn about them through their actions and words. Show us their dreams, their fears, and their everyday life.

I look at two news shows from Columbus, Ohio. The first was NBC 4 this morning (August 13, 2011). It was live. The main story was about a man in Ashley, Ohio. He hurt his wife.  Her name was not said, but his name was Shad Hostettler. They showed his picture. He looked bad. They talked about this story for two minutes. They said he hurt his wife many times and was arrested. I think they talked about it for the right amount of time. 

The next story was about a man named Travis Buyers. He was 18 years old. He was shot in the morning in Sharon Woods. He was hurt badly. No one had been arrested. The SWAT team was looking into it. This story was short. I think this is because he was a black man or lived in a black neighborhood. I have seen this before. The news does not talk much about crimes against black people. White people are talked about more.

The next story was about a hole in a helicopter.  The hole was from a gun. They said it was a small bullet from a gun. They gave money to help find the person who shot the helicopter.

Then they talked about the rain coming on Saturday. They said the weather would be warm. They did not talk about it for long. They wanted to make you watch more.

They also talked about a robbery at a store in Columbus. A black man robbed the store. He was tall and thin. They said he was black a lot.

The last story was about a man named Rene Rodriguez. He was from Texas. He sold a lot of drugs in Ohio. He went to prison for a long time. They said he was Hispanic. This did not seem important.

Brothers have a strong bond. This bond is very important. It has many feelings: love, pride, jealousy, and anger. Brothers know each other very well. They see themselves in their brother.

This bond is most strong when things are bad. The true nature of the bond shows. It can be good or bad. These feelings have a big cost.

To understand the feelings between brothers, we must see the results. When you look at your brother, you see yourself. You see yourself as you truly are. Your actions and the results show your real character.

In "The Scarlet Ibis", two brothers show this theme. They have many strong feelings.  

In a beautiful place, the brothers go on a journey. They fail. At the end, there is sadness and pride. One brother lives.

The story shows the feelings of the main character, Doodle. It shows how he feels about his brother. The story also shows how the main character sees the world. These things affect his actions.

The main character feels pride. From the time he and Doodle go out together, he feels sad about Doodle. He wanted a brother to teach. He wanted a brother to play with. Doodle is sick and cannot do these things. 

The main character is angry at Doodle. He thinks about hurting Doodle. But he sees Doodle smile, and he feels love.

The brain is very complex. It is good at thinking and making new things. As technology got better, people used new words to talk about the brain. First they said it was like a tablet, then like paper, then like a book, and now like a computer. But these words are not perfect. They can make people think wrong things.

The brain takes in information from our senses. Our senses feel things like touch, heat, sound, and light. The brain turns these feelings into signals. The brain uses these signals to understand the world.

When we see a black box on a white background, the brain looks at the colors, shapes, and edges. This helps us see the box. The brain also uses what it already knows to help us see the box. For example, it knows that boxes are usually solid, not holes.

The brain also pays attention to important things. It looks at everything, but it focuses on what is important. We might not notice each blade of grass, but we notice our name when someone says it.

The brain stores information in different ways. Some information is short-term, like when we remember a phone number for a few seconds. Other information is long-term, like our name and birthday. The brain stores information in different parts and uses it later.

There are many ways to learn about how the brain works. Some people study how people remember things. Others study computers. Others study the brain itself. One idea is that the brain stores information like a network of ideas. Each idea is connected to other ideas. For example, the idea of "chair" is connected to the idea of "table" and "wood".

Aldous Huxley writes about a bad future. In his book, "Brave New World," people are happy but not free. They live in a world where the government controls everything. People are taught to be happy and not care about others. They do not think for themselves.  They only want to have fun.

Huxley is worried about new technology and how it can be used to control people. He also worries about how money can be used to control people. He uses his book to show how bad these things can be.  

The book shows how people can be tricked into being happy even if they are not free. The people in the book do not know that they are being controlled. They think they are happy, but they are not.

Huxley uses ideas from Karl Marx to show how bad this future could be. Marx believed that rich people control poor people by making them think that they are happy. This is called "false consciousness."

In "Brave New World," the government controls the people by making them watch television and buy things. The people are happy because they are distracted by these things. They do not think about the fact that they are being controlled.

I go to school at University Park for two and a half years. I live in a dorm. It is far from the center of campus. Walking to class can take a long time, maybe twenty five minutes. I talk to a school alum. They said that the area near my dorm used to be empty. Now it has new buildings. The campus is getting bigger. It is hard to get around.

What is the best way to get around? A bike is good. But the campus needs to be good for bikes.

My friend just started riding a bike again. He said bikes are good.

Bikes are good for your body. They are also fast. A small meal and some exercise can take you far.

I live off campus. It is far from the center. I bought a bike.

It takes twenty five minutes to walk to my class. On a bike, it takes five minutes.

But the road is not good for bikes. I like to walk, but I am busy. Without a bike, I would walk. Walking to class every day takes a long time.

I do not have that time.
